## In plain words

Convergio is built to help solopreneurs grow. The code is open for everyone
to read, learn from, and use. We believe in trust, not paywalls.

If Convergio helps you, we ask one thing: **help someone who needs it**.

---

## You can

- **Use** Convergio for any personal, educational, or commercial purpose,
  subject to the restrictions below.
- **Read, study, and learn** from the source code.
- **Modify** the code for your own use.
- **Contribute** improvements back to the project.
- **Fork and redistribute** Convergio — modified or unmodified — as long
  as this license stays attached in its entirety and all its terms
  (including restrictions and donation request) remain unchanged.

## We ask

If you use Convergio and it brings value to your work or your business,
consider making a donation to **FightTheStroke Foundation**
(fightthestroke.org) — a non-profit that supports children and families
affected by pediatric stroke and cerebral palsy.

This is not a legal obligation. It's an invitation. We trust you.

Donations are entirely voluntary and do not create any contractual
relationship, entitlement to support, warranty, or any other obligation
beyond those stated in this license. A donation does not constitute
payment for the software and does not modify the terms of this license
in any way. Donations are made directly to FightTheStroke Foundation.
Roberto D'Angelo and the Convergio project do not receive, manage, or
benefit financially from these donations.

## Always free for

- **Students** (anyone currently enrolled in a recognized educational
  institution) — no questions asked.
- **People with disabilities** — no questions asked.
- **Non-profit organizations** (any organization recognized as non-profit
  or charitable under the laws of its jurisdiction) — no questions asked.

No registration, no proof, no paperwork. We trust you.

## You cannot

- **Sell** Convergio as a product, or as part of a product where Convergio
  provides a substantial portion of the product's functionality.
- **Host** Convergio as a managed, hosted, or "as-a-service" offering for
  external third parties — meaning you may not provide Convergio's features
  to others over a network as a commercial service. Using Convergio
  internally within your own organization is permitted.
- **Remove** this license or copyright notice from the code.
- **Claim** Convergio as your own work.

If you want to do any of the above, we're happy to talk:
licensing@convergio.io

Our trust in you does not constitute a waiver of any rights under this
license.

## Professional services

Want help getting the most out of Convergio? We offer consulting,
workshops, and speaking engagements — priced based on the value we create
together, not by the hour.

Reach out: convergio.io

